Q: What is less?
Less = The dynamic stylesheet language.
LESS extends CSS with dynamic behavior such as variables, mixins, operations and functions. 
LESS runs on both the client-side (Chrome, Safari, Firefox) and server-side, with Node.js and Rhino. 

Q: What is a CSS preprocessor?
- variables, functions, and classes

==> compile less file and output is a css file!

Q: When is less run?
Node can compile less at runtime and on demand

Q: What is the command line?
lessc
lessc yourLessFile.less > yourCssFile.css

Q: Is there a GUI interface?
Crunch: but only supported on windows and OSX because using Adobe air!

Q: Tell me about variables?
They start with the @ sign
They are at the head of the file and reused through out the file


